  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"/home/ubuntu/py-evm/venv/bin/trinity\", line 11, in <module>\r\n    load_entry_point('py-evm', 'console_scripts', 'trinity')()\r\n  File \"/home/ubuntu/py-evm/trinity/main.py\", line 101, in main\r\n    initialize_data_dir(chain_config)\r\n  File \"/home/ubuntu/py-evm/trinity/chains/__init__.py\", line 88, in initialize_data_dir\r\n    chain_config.data_dir,\r\nValueError: The base chain directory provided does not exist: `//$HOME/.local/share/trinity/mainnet`\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf the `$HOME` environment variable isn't set Trinity crashes.\r\n\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nGracefully handle this not being set and provide a helpful error message informing the user that they can:\r\n\r\n- set `$HOME` to the desired path.\r\n- set `$XDG_TRINITY_HOME` to the desired path.\r\n- set `$TRINITY_DATA_DIR` to the desired path.\r\n- run trinity with the `--data-dir /some/path` where `/some/path` is the desired path.\r\n\r\nAll of these should be tested to work as solutions. ",
